<p>I'm not able to upload a file whithin my android app. I'm using Google Application Engine and Google Cloud Storage. The app has been signed. The sha1 fingerprint has been written in a client id credential join with de package name. I test it in a real device, not in a emulated deviced. The code is:</p>  <pre><code>private static String BUCKET= "***********.appspot.com"; private final GcsService gcsService = GcsServiceFactory.createGcsService(RetryParams.getDefaultInstance());   GcsFilename mGcsFilename = new GcsFilename(BUCKET,file_name);  MimetypesFileTypeMap mimeTypesMap = new MimetypesFileTypeMap(); String mimeType = mimeTypesMap.getContentType(file_path);  GcsFileOptions options = new GcsFileOptions.Builder().mimeType(mimeType).acl("project-private").build();  GcsOutputChannel outputChannel = gcsService.createOrReplace(mGcsFilename, options); </code></pre>  <p>It throws RetriesExhaustedException exception when createorreplace is called.</p>  <p>What am I doing wrong? </p>